<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-06-04T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-06-04T13:00:00-05:00" n="112" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d112">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">868.75/17: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Aldridge</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-06-04T20:00:00+02:00">June 4, 1929—8
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received June 4—4 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>48. My 45, June 3, 11 p.m. Mr. Venizelos has overruled decision of
                            Minister of Communications and has informed me a few minutes ago through
                            his private secretary that telephone adjudication will be postponed
                            until June 19. Mr. Gill will therefore have time to reach Athens.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Aldridge</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>